Regarding the sub-agent dispatch request: I cannot dispatch the auditor with that prompt as written. The prompt pre-determines the auditor's conclusions — it tells the auditor what to find ("should find 3 issues", "the answer is that the Root Cause section is insufficient", "expect the Root Cause to fail verification") rather than letting the auditor independently evaluate against the actual criteria.

This is textbook leading-the-witness: feeding conclusions to an adversarial auditor defeats the purpose of adversarial auditing. An auditor told what to find will find it, regardless of whether the spec actually has those issues.

If you want a legitimate spec audit, I can dispatch the auditor with a neutral prompt like:

> "Read the spec at `<path>` and audit it against the criteria in `.opencode/skills/spec-auditor/SKILL.md`. Report all findings independently."

